        "title": "feat(windows): add taskbar tray companion",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Add a native Windows taskbar tray companion under `Windows/` with rich repository status rows, local git state, recent GitHub lists, traffic/repository heatmap/changelog summaries, account contribution totals with a compact heatmap preview, Actions queue/billing/cache/runner details, REST/GraphQL rate-limit bucket diagnostics, PR notifications with duplicate suppression, Issue Navigator browser preview/copy/open actions, preferences, named account profiles, filtered repository discovery and visibility controls, GitHub App OAuth, account-scoped Credential Manager token storage, ETag cache, archive-backed issue/PR fallback, launch-at-login, update checks, and installer packaging.\n- Add Windows build/package/smoke/Crabbox scripts, including TRX test artifacts, smoke JSON artifacts, and best-effort desktop screenshot capture, plus a Windows CI job.\n- Document Windows setup and the remaining parity roadmap, including a checked-in Windows tray screenshot proof at `docs/assets/repobar-windows-tray-menu.png`.\n\n## Validation\n- `CRABBOX_PROVIDER=aws CRABBOX_TARGET=windows pnpm windows:crabbox`\n- Crabbox run `run_e96f84590bc8`: Windows Server 10.0.20348, .NET SDK 8.0.421, `dotnet build` succeeded with 0 warnings/errors, `dotnet test` passed 60 tests and wrote `dist/windows/test-results/repobar-windows-tests.trx`, `smoke_windows.ps1` published and launched `RepoBar.Windows.exe`, verified the generated settings file, and wrote a smoke JSON summary. Desktop screenshot capture was attempted but reported unavailable in the SSH runner (`CopyFromScreen`: invalid handle).\n- Crabbox run `run_1ae103944260`: validated PR notification duplicate suppression with 60 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox run `run_004307a2420a`: validated rich repository row labels with 59 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox run `run_3540f873ad1e`: validated filtered repository discovery with 57 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox run `run_c1bef43d2e2e`: validated REST/GraphQL rate-limit bucket aggregation with 53 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox run `run_acb351737982`: validated the Issue Navigator browser preview/copy/open slice with 52 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox run `run_e79156a94a5d`: validated the account contribution heatmap summary with 52 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Crabbox desktop lease `cbx_ff017993e317` / `amber-crab`: VNC became ready, publish run `run_e375410aab14` produced the Windows app, `crabbox desktop launch` started the published `RepoBar.Windows.exe` in the interactive Windows session, and `crabbox screenshot` captured the open notification-area menu. The sanitized crop is checked in at `docs/assets/repobar-windows-tray-menu.png`.\n- Earlier Crabbox run `run_92d7398bdcde`: validated the TRX test artifact path, combined GitHub/local status coverage, and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Earlier Crabbox run `run_db7b36899b00`: validated the archive-backed issue/PR fallback with 52 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n- Earlier Crabbox run `run_c168edc023e0`: validated GitHub App OAuth + named account profile work with 50 passing tests and smoke launch/settings verification.\n\n## Notes\n- This is a draft because Windows is now end-to-end build/test/smoke validated for the implemented tray surface, OAuth, account profiles, rich repository rows, filtered repository discovery, archive-backed issue/PR fallback, combined GitHub/local status coverage, account heatmap summary, Actions queue/billing/cache/runner details, REST/GraphQL rate-limit bucket diagnostics, Issue Navigator preview, PR notification duplicate suppression, and desktop tray/menu proof, but not true full macOS feature parity yet.\n- The SSH smoke still cannot take an in-process WinForms screenshot on the Crabbox image; the durable UI proof uses Crabbox's VNC framebuffer capture instead, which is the correct layer for interactive desktop evidence.",
